wikipedia_page.main: Montford George Southall (17 July 1907–2 May 1993) was a British track cyclist. He won a bronze medal at the 1928 Summer Olympics in the team pursuit event.He was born in the Wandsworth district of London and died in Waveney, Suffolk.
